-- England Leads Pakistan by 419 Runs After Third Day of Opening Cricket Test
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-07-31T18:17:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-31/england-leads-pakistan-by-419-runs-after-third-day-of-opening-cricket-test.html

          
          
             England leads Pakistan by 419 runs
after day three of their first cricket Test at Trent Bridge in
Nottingham.  
 Matt Prior was 102 not out as England declared on 262-9 in
its second innings, setting Pakistan a record chase of 435 for
victory. The visitors then stumbled to 15-3 at stumps as Stuart
Broad took two wickets and James Anderson claimed one.  
 Prior hit seven fours and two sixes in recording his third
Test century.  
 Pakistan was bowled out for 182 this morning after resuming
on 147-9. England scored 354 in its first innings after winning
the toss and electing to bat.  
          
          


  


        